  "text": "III. CNN-BASED VISUAL SERVOING CONTROL SCHEME The aim of a camera/end-effector positioning task is to reach a desired pose r * starting from an arbitrary initial pose r (both ∈ se(3)). Image-based visual servoing (IBVS) is a method to control camera motion to minimize the positioning error between r and r * in the image space [CITATION_1] .",
